===Adjective===
{{en-adj|er|more}}

# [[uncomplicated|Uncomplicated]]; taken by itself, with nothing added.
#* {{RQ:EHough PrqsPrc|I|0088}}
#*: “[…] We are engaged in a great work, a treatise on our river fortifications, perhaps? But since when did army officers afford the luxury of amanuenses in this '''simple''' republic?{{nb...}}”
#* '''2001''', Sydney I. Landau, ''Dictionaries: The Art and Craft of Lexicography'', Cambridge University Press {{ISBN|0-521-78512-X}}, page 167,
#*: There is no '''simple''' way to define precisely a complex arrangement of parts, however homely the object may appear to be.
# Without [[ornamentation]]; [[plain]].
# Free from [[duplicity]]; [[guileless]], [[innocent]], [[straightforward]].
#* {{w|John Marston (poet)|John Marston}} (ca.1576-1634)
#*: Full many fine men go upon my score, as '''simple''' as I stand here, and I trust them.
#* {{w|Lord Byron}} (1788-1824)
#*: Must thou trust Tradition's '''simple''' tongue?
#* {{w|Ralph Waldo Emerson}} (1803-1882)
