# {{lb|en|now|rare}} [[trivial|Trivial]]; [[insignificant]].
#* '''1485''', {{w|Thomas Malory}}, ''{{w|Le Morte d'Arthur}}'', Book X:
#*: ‘That was a '''symple''' cause,’ seyde Sir Trystram, ‘for to sle a good knyght for seyynge well by his maystir.’
# {{lb|en|now|colloquial}} Feeble-minded; [[foolish]].
# {{lb|en|heading|technical}} Structurally uncomplicated.
